  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "fe641243-f901-456d-88b9-a213a6ef4bba",
    "name": "Groq API",
    "description": "The Groq API is designed to optimize the orchestration of multiple AI agents, enabling them to work as a cohesive team to accomplish complex tasks and create sophisticated workflows. With Groq's fast inference speeds, developers can achieve rapid autonomous decision-making and collaboration among agent teams. The API supports scalable multi-agent systems, allowing multiple agents to run in parallel without performance degradation. Integration is straightforward, requiring just a few lines of code to get started. For more detailed information, you can refer to the [Official Documentation: CrewAI](https://docs.crewai.com/concepts/llms) and the [Groq API Cookbook: CrewAI Mixture of Agents Tutorial](https://github.com/groq/groq-api-cookbook/tree/main/tutorials/crewai-mixture-of-agents). The Groq API is mostly compatible with OpenAI's client libraries, making it easy to configure your existing applications to run on Groq and try our inference speed.\n\n# Security\n\nThe Groq API is secured using an API key mechanism. This means that each request to the API must include a valid API key for authentication purposes. This approach ensures that only authorized users can access the API resources.\n\nBefore you can make any API calls, you need to obtain an API key from the Groq developer portal. Once you have your API key, you should set it as an environment variable named `GROQ_API_KEY`. This setup is crucial for authenticating your requests. More details can be found in the [API Reference](https://docs.groq.com/docs/api-reference).\n\n# How to use this collection\n\nTo use this Postman collection, you need to set up an environment variable for the API key. This will allow you to authenticate your requests seamlessly. Below is a table describing the necessary environment variable:\n\n| Name          | Description                                      |\n|---------------|--------------------------------------------------|\n| GROQ_API_KEY  | Your Groq API key used for authenticating requests. |\n\nEnsure that you replace the placeholder with your actual API key value. It's recommended to use the Postman vault for storing sensitive information like API keys. You can learn more about the vault [here](https://learning.postman.com/docs/sending-requests/postman-vault/postman-vault-secrets/).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "31008811",
    "_collection_link": "https://go.postman.co/collection/42654973-fe641243-f901-456d-88b9-a213a6ef4bba?source=collection_link"
  },
